    <!-- Tutorial screen -->
    <string name="tutorial_title">How to Use Photobooth</string>
    <string name="tutorial_back">Back</string>
    <string name="tutorial_next">Next</string>
    <string name="tutorial_done">Get Started</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_welcome_title">Welcome to Photobooth</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_welcome_body">Photobooth is built for events: set up your event once, start the camera, then let guests capture, share, print, and replay the tutorial whenever they need it.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_permissions_title">Permissions</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_permissions_body">The app asks for **camera** access to take photos, **microphone** access for videos, and **media** access to save captures. Photos and videos stay on this device unless you upload or share them.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_home_title">Home Screen</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_home_body">Use **Start Photobooth** for the camera, **View Gallery** for finished photos, **Settings** for event setup, and **Tutorial** to replay these instructions any time. If you have not unlocked unlimited photos, **Get More Photos** opens ad rewards and purchase options.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_capture_title">Taking Photos</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_capture_body">Position everyone in the live preview and tap the round **Capture** button. A three-second countdown plays, the app says Smile, flashes the screen, saves the photo, and updates your daily photo counter.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_quota_title">Daily Photo Limit</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_quota_body">Each day starts with **15 free photos**. Watch a rewarded ad to add **15 more photos**, up to **75 total photos per day**. Buy **Unlimited Photos** once for $9.99 to remove the daily limit and hide the counter.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_booth_title">Booth Mode</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_booth_body">Enable **Booth Mode** in Settings to take 2 to 8 photos in one session. The camera pauses briefly between shots and shows the session count on screen.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_templates_title">Photo Templates</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_templates_body">Choose a built-in layout such as **single portrait**, **2x2 grid**, or **vertical strip**. Templates give event photos a finished layout before they reach the gallery.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_gif_title">Animated GIFs</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_gif_body">In Booth Mode, turn on **Create animated GIF**. The app keeps the individual photos and adds a GIF version of the full booth sequence to the gallery.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_filters_title">Photo Filters</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_filters_body">Pick a filter in Settings before capture. Options include **Original**, **Grayscale**, **Sepia**, **B&amp;W**, **Vintage**, **Cool**, **Warm**, and **Vivid**.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_frames_title">Custom Frames</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_frames_body">Use **Manage Frames** to import transparent PNG overlays. Select a frame in Settings and it will be applied to new captures.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_watermark_title">Watermarks &amp; Logos</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_watermark_body">Enable **Watermark / Logo**, enter the image path, and choose its position. This brands new photos with your event or company mark.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_gallery_title">Photo Gallery</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_gallery_body">The **Gallery** stores captured photos, GIFs, and videos. Tap an item to preview it, upload it, or use the sharing options available for that media type.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_upload_title">Cloud Upload</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_upload_body">Tap **Upload** from a gallery item. By default, uploads use an anonymous temporary host; configure **Immich** in Settings if you want self-hosted storage.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_qr_title">QR Code Sharing</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_qr_body">After an upload succeeds, the gallery detail shows a **QR code** for the uploaded URL. Guests can scan it to open the shared photo, GIF, or video.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_share_title">Sharing</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_share_body">Use **SMS** and **Email** after configuring your gateway or SMTP settings. Use **Share to Apps** for the Android share sheet.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_print_title">Printing</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_print_body">Tap **Print** from a gallery item to use Android printing. Choose any printer or print service already available on the device.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_settings_title">Settings</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_settings_body">Settings control the event name, filenames, camera, video capture, booth mode, GIF mode, filters, templates, frames, watermark, upload destination, SMS, and email.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_privacy_title">Privacy</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_privacy_body">Photos and credentials are stored locally. Analytics and crash reporting only run if you allow them during the consent prompt.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_support_title">Support</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_support_body">The **Support Charles on Buy Me a Coffee** link opens a browser page. It is always optional and stays below the main controls on the Home screen.</string>

    <!-- Privacy policy screen -->
    <string name="privacy_policy_title">Privacy Policy</string>
    <string name="privacy_policy_content"><![CDATA[
        <h3>Photobooth Privacy Policy</h3>
        <p><b>Last updated:</b> May 2026</p>
        <p>This privacy policy applies to the Photobooth mobile application.</p>
        <h4>Information We Collect</h4>
        <p><b>Photos and videos:</b> All captures are stored locally on your device. We do not transmit, access, or store your captures on any external server unless you explicitly configure an upload destination (such as Immich) in the app settings.</p>
        <p><b>Crash Reports:</b> If you grant consent, we collect anonymous crash reports via Firebase Crashlytics to help us fix bugs. These reports contain device information (model, OS version) and stack traces — no personal data.</p>
        <p><b>Usage Analytics:</b> If you grant consent, we collect anonymous usage statistics via Firebase Analytics to understand how the app is used (e.g., screen visits, feature usage). No personally identifiable information is collected.</p>
        <h4>Information You Configure</h4>
        <p>You may optionally configure:<br/>
        • SMTP credentials for sending emails<br/>
        • SMS gateway credentials for sending text messages<br/>
        • Immich server credentials for photo uploads</p>
        <p>These credentials are stored locally on your device using encrypted storage. They are never transmitted to us or any third party except the services you explicitly configure.</p>
        <h4>Data Sharing</h4>
        <p>We do not sell, trade, or share your personal data with any third parties.</p>
        <h4>Data Retention</h4>
        <p>All photos and settings remain on your device until you delete them. Uninstalling the app removes all local data.</p>
        <h4>Children\'s Privacy</h4>
        <p>This app does not knowingly collect data from children under 13.</p>
        <h4>Your Rights</h4>
        <p>You may opt out of analytics at any time. To do so, navigate to Settings in the app.</p>
        <h4>Contact</h4>
        <p>If you have questions about this policy, please contact the developer.</p>
    ]]></string>
